ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the binding interaction of PA@N-GQD with the radioactive elements, we evaluate the changes in the fluorescence emission of PA@N-GQD (50 × 10−6 M) upon the successive addition of U(VI) and Th(IV) ions (10 × 10−6 M to 100 × 10−6 M) separately, in H2O (Fig. 3
                        ). Upon increasing the concentration of U(VI) and Th(IV) ions, the consistent decrease in the fluorescence emission of PA@N-GQD at 438 nm (λ
                        ex: 344 nm) indicates a substantial binding interaction between U(VI) and Th(IV) ions with PA@N-GQD. The significant quenching of PA@N-GQD's fluorescence intensity by both U(VI) and Th(IV) is associated with either static or dynamic quenching caused by U(VI) ions and a combination of static or dynamic quenching caused by Th(IV) ions.
